# Week 4 - LoRA Fine-Tuning for Brand Style

## Intern

Anjal Suryawanshi

## Project

AI-Powered Fashion Design Assistant with Generative Models

## Objectives

* Understand LoRA fine-tuning workflow
* Explore fashion brand aesthetics
* Implement prompt-token based style switching
* Generate style-specific fashion designs
* Evaluate outputs using CLIP similarity metrics

## Technologies Used

* Python
* Stable Diffusion
* Hugging Face Diffusers
* CLIP
* PyTorch

## Outputs

1. Cyberpunk Techwear Style Design
2. Minimalist Haute Couture Style Design

## Evaluation

Generated images were evaluated using CLIP similarity scores to measure alignment between generated fashion designs and target style descriptions.

## Learning Outcomes

* Understanding of LoRA architecture
* Style conditioning through prompt engineering
* CLIP-based image-text evaluation
* Fashion AI workflow development
